    "attributes": {
        "action": "Debate the removal of the right of British citizens abroad to pay class 2 NICs",
        "additional_details": "Some British citizens abroad are in low paid jobs with local salaries, and may not have been in their country of residence long enough to accrue a reasonable pension there. We also believe that we carry out cultural diplomacy and promote Britain. ",
        "background": "British citizens abroad will no longer be able to pay class 2 national insurance contributions to obtain a UK State pension. This has been in place until now, and UK citizens may have planned their future financial security around this scheme.",
